This paper focuses on the design of an online participatory-democracy platform, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (HCI), computer-supported cooperative work (CSCW), and social informatics (SI). The study also analyzes the effectiveness of the platform in promoting deliberative decision making, which could fall under the category of digital libraries (DL) or cybernetics (CY).
